main event: A round, dark green, brown or black object was sighted near Sahuarita, Arizona on February 25, 1956.
interesting points: The object was about twice the diameter of a utility pole and moved silently towards the north.
The Air Force initially evaluated the sighting as a 'probable balloon', but later could not find records of any balloons in the area at that time.
The witness drew sketches of the object as seen with the naked eye and through binoculars.
The witness estimated the object's speed to be between 1,500-2,000 mph and its distance to be 1-3 miles away.
The witness compared the object's appearance to that of a 'triangular object pulled by a parachute or kite', but could not explain its origin or destination.
sighted object: round, dark green, brown or black object
